From: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
Subject: [PATCH] ath11k: skip monitor status reap until the ring is initialized

During firmware recovery the extended interrupt groups are re-enabled
before the monitor status refill ring has been set up again. Servicing
the ring in that window passes an uninitialized srng (hp_addr == NULL)
to ath11k_hal_srng_access_begin() and panics in interrupt context -
observed deterministically on IPQ8074 with NSS offload: every firmware
fatal (hif_ce.c assertion -> Q6 SSR) turned into a host kernel panic
about one second into the recovery, from the napi thread:

  ath11k_hal_srng_access_begin+0xc
  ath11k_dp_rx_process_mon_status+0x15c
  ath11k_dp_service_srng+0xb8
  ath11k_ahb_ext_grp_napi_poll+0x34

Because the panic fires in the recovery path, it converts every
recoverable firmware crash into a reboot. Check the srng's initialized
flag (set by ath11k_hal_srng_setup, the same flag the HAL debug dump
path already gates on) and skip the reap until the ring is live again.

Signed-off-by: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/dp_rx.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/dp_rx.c
@@ -4046,6 +4046,16 @@ static int ath11k_dp_rx_reap_mon_status_
 
 	srng = &ab->hal.srng_list[rx_ring->refill_buf_ring.ring_id];
 
+	/*
+	 * During firmware recovery the extended interrupt groups are
+	 * re-enabled before the monitor status ring is set up again;
+	 * servicing it in that window dereferences an uninitialized srng
+	 * (hp_addr == NULL) and panics in interrupt context. Skip until
+	 * the ring is live again.
+	 */
+	if (!srng->initialized)
+		return 0;
+
 	spin_lock_bh(&srng->lock);
 
 	ath11k_hal_srng_access_begin(ab, srng);
